features: 【Sturdy and Durable】This robust full size bed frame is crafted of metal slats, side rails and 10 sturdy legs, with a maximum weight capacity of 600 lb, ensuring you a restful night's sleep free of squeaky noise. The 12 metal slats set between two sides provide strong support for your mattress (no box spring required).

【Standard Full Bed】Overall sizes include width: 57’’, length: 78’’ and height: 35’’. This wrought iron bed is designed to fit standard US full mattress sizes, no matter it is memory foam, latex, hybrid or spring type.

【Industrial Style】The mix of clean lines and metallic finish creates a simple but stylish tone that will perfectly blend with industrial, rustic and farmhouse-styled homes. Any type of bedding will go well with this modern chic bed frame.

【Ample Under-Bed Storage】The 11.2 inches of clearance under the bed brings you extra storage space for cases, storage boxes or other supplies. The lightweight design of this platform bed makes it convenient to move around as needed.

【Easy Assembly】We provide all the necessary hardware and tool, and an illustrated installation manual to help you set up this metal bed frame. Should you have any questions, please feel free to contact us!

reviews.reviewText: as you are reading this, I am writing it on my own bed frame which I am reviewing, it is comfortable and I haven't changed it since I got it, I had a small problem with the shipping, but it was resolved quickly, but in all its a great bed frame I do recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I've had this bed for about a year now. I really like them and they're easy to put together. My only issue is that the bars bend really easily. My two boys have been jumping on their bed and I saw the bars underneath the mattress are bent. So it's not really sturdy and I imagine I'll have to get a new bed soon

reviews.reviewTitle: Not the best but not the worst. Good for your money.
reviews.reviewText: You do get what you pay for. While it is a very sturdy bed and relatively easy to build (don’t be intimidated by other reviews, ikea furniture is MUCH more intense). Upon building it a few of the threads were relatively defective and hard to maneuver (a mallet got the job done) but nonetheless we built the bed in an hour and a half and it is VERY sturdy all things considered.
